    public class Folder

      • findChild

        public Hierarchy findChild(java.lang.String path)
                    throws fileNotFound
        Method to follow a path in the current Hierarchy and return the Hierarchy element at the given path will be used in every method that need to access a specific directory or file in the hierarchy
        Parameters:
        path - : path must be a string like "/folder1/subfold1/file.extension" or "C:\\folder1\\subfold1\\file.extension"
        Returns:
        the Hierarchy element at the given path, if it exists
        Throws:
        fileNotFound

      • alreadyExist

        public void alreadyExist(java.lang.String name)
